WEBVTT

00:40.749 --> 00:43.332
<i>Oh, fuck.</i>

00:51.552 --> 00:54.420
- Uh, yeah?
- Miles, can you move your car, please?

00:54.555 --> 00:57.423
- Why?
- Because the roofers gotta get the truck in.

00:57.558 --> 01:00.016
- You didn't park too good. Okay?
- Yeah. All right.

01:00.102 --> 01:02.094
Hold on.

01:21.832 --> 01:24.745
Sorry.
Sorry, gentlemen.

01:24.835 --> 01:26.997
Sorry.

01:58.744 --> 02:01.111
Oh, fuck me!

02:01.204 --> 02:04.368
<i>I know I said
I would be there by noon,</i>

02:04.458 --> 02:08.293
but, uh, there's all of this work
going on at my building,

02:08.377 --> 02:10.791
and it's just
a total nightmare.

02:10.881 --> 02:14.295
I had a bunch of stuff
I had to deal with this morning,

02:14.384 --> 02:16.296
but I'm on my way.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.878
I'm out the door right now.

02:35.405 --> 02:37.146
<i>- Hi, Simon.
- Hey, Miles.</i>

02:37.240 --> 02:39.152
<i>- Triple espresso, please.</i>
- For here?

02:39.242 --> 02:42.155
Uh, no, actually.
I'm running late. Make it to go.

02:42.245 --> 02:45.158
And give me a <i>New York Times</i>
and a spinach croissant.

02:45.248 --> 02:46.864
Thank you.

03:54.025 --> 03:55.891
- Ah!
- Well, hello!

03:56.027 --> 03:58.235
- Hello, Mrs. Erganian. How are you?
- Come on in.

03:58.363 --> 04:01.322
- Thank you. Is Jack still here?
- Yes.

04:04.786 --> 04:08.200
<i>Shot on the way to the 118.</i>

04:10.792 --> 04:12.658
Look what the cat dragged.

04:12.794 --> 04:15.707
- Hi, everybody. Sorry.
- Hey.

04:15.797 --> 04:17.709
Somebody finally arrived.

04:17.798 --> 04:19.665
You finally got here.
Mr. Prompt.

04:19.801 --> 04:22.714
- Oh, remember my kids? Alex, Helen?
- Hi. How are you?

04:22.804 --> 04:26.172
<i>We were thinking maybe you went
the wrong way, you went to Tijuana...</i>

04:26.308 --> 04:28.174
- Right.
- and they don't let you back.

04:28.310 --> 04:30.176
- Yes! Yes!
- Daddy!

04:30.312 --> 04:33.225
- I had to bribe them.
- Hey, Miles.

04:33.315 --> 04:35.181
Hey. How are you,
Christine?

04:35.317 --> 04:37.183
Yeah, the freeway was unbelievable.

04:37.319 --> 04:40.232
- Unbelievable. It was bumper-to-bumper the whole way.
- Sure, sure.

04:40.322 --> 04:43.235
People getting an early start
on the weekend, I guess.

04:43.325 --> 04:45.191
Granted, I got
a late start, but...

04:45.327 --> 04:47.740
- Well, we're just glad you made it.
- Yes.

04:47.829 --> 04:50.196
Christine, why don't you
ask Miles about the cake?

04:50.332 --> 04:52.244
- Oh, good idea. Come with me.
- What's this?

04:52.334 --> 04:55.202
We don't really have time for that,
'cause we gotta hit the road.

04:55.337 --> 04:58.501
- <i>Oh, come on! It's just gonna take a second!</i>
- Yeah.

04:58.590 --> 05:01.082
<i>Mmm.</i>

05:01.176 --> 05:03.293
Jack tells us you are publishing a book.
Congratulations.

05:03.428 --> 05:06.341
- Uh...
- Yes, congratulations.

05:06.431 --> 05:10.175
Yes, well, uh, it's not exactly
finalized yet.

05:10.310 --> 05:13.769
- So... There has been some interest, and...
- Your friend is modest.

05:13.855 --> 05:17.019
Oh, come on, Miles. Don't be so modest.
Indulge them.

05:17.150 --> 05:20.314
<i>- Don't make me out to be a liar.
- What is the subject of your book?</i>

05:20.445 --> 05:22.687
- Nonfiction?
<i>- Uh, no. It's... It's a novel.</i>

05:22.823 --> 05:25.065
<i>- Fiction. Yes.</i>
- Oh.

05:25.158 --> 05:28.071
Although there is quite a bit
from my own life,

05:28.161 --> 05:31.074
so I suppose that, technically,
some of it is nonfiction.

05:31.164 --> 05:33.406
<i>Good.
I like nonfiction.</i>

05:33.500 --> 05:35.913
There is so much to know
about this world.

05:36.002 --> 05:39.461
I think you read something somebody
just invented it, waste of time.

05:40.966 --> 05:42.832
That's an interesting
perspective.

05:42.968 --> 05:46.336
- So, which one do you like better?
- Oh, well, I like them both.

05:46.429 --> 05:49.843
But, um, if pressed,
I would have to say that I prefer the dark.

05:49.975 --> 05:52.342
<i>Told ya!</i>

05:52.477 --> 05:54.719
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

06:01.528 --> 06:03.440
Bye.

06:09.786 --> 06:11.698
Bye.

06:11.788 --> 06:14.656
Where the fuck were you, man? Huh?
I was dying in there.

06:14.791 --> 06:17.955
- We're supposed to be a hundred miles away by now.
- I can't help the traffic.

06:18.044 --> 06:20.957
Oh, come on. You're fucking hungover.
You know you are.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.630
Okay, there was
a tasting last night, yes.

06:23.717 --> 06:27.461
But I wanted to get us something nice
for the ride up. Check out the box.

06:27.554 --> 06:30.422
Why did you tell them that my novel
was being published?

06:30.557 --> 06:34.221
- 'Cause you said you had it all lined up.
- No, I didn't. No. No.

06:34.311 --> 06:37.600
What I said was that there was
some interest at Conundrum.

06:37.731 --> 06:41.645
- Yeah. Conundrum.
- And that one of the editors was passing it to a senior editor.

06:41.735 --> 06:44.148
Sounds pretty good to me.
Sounds like you're in.

06:44.237 --> 06:46.149
No. It's a long shot.

06:46.239 --> 06:49.732
Besides, Conundrum, it's just a small
specialty press.

06:49.826 --> 06:51.738
I'm not gonna
get my hopes up.

06:51.828 --> 06:53.740
You know?
I've stopped caring.

06:53.830 --> 06:56.743
The hell with it.
I have stopped caring.

06:56.833 --> 07:00.042
It sounds like it's gonna happen this time.
I mean, I can feel it.

07:00.128 --> 07:02.541
I think this is the one.
Huh?

07:02.631 --> 07:04.497
I'm really proud
of you, man.

07:04.633 --> 07:06.625
- Don't open that now. It's warm.
- Why not?

07:06.718 --> 07:10.837
Jack, that is a 1992 Byron.
It's really rare. Okay?

07:10.972 --> 07:13.464
- I've been saving it. Don't...
- All right. I won't open it.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.512
Jack!

07:15.602 --> 07:17.719
Half of it gone.

07:17.812 --> 07:21.226
Hey, shut up.
Okay?

07:21.316 --> 07:24.184
Here's to a great week.

07:24.319 --> 07:26.311
Come on.

07:27.948 --> 07:30.156
Yes. Absolutely.

07:30.241 --> 07:32.153
Despite your crass behavior,

07:32.243 --> 07:34.451
I'm actually glad we're getting
this time together.

07:34.537 --> 07:36.449
Yeah. Me too.

07:36.539 --> 07:39.407
I've been looking forward
to this for a long time.

07:39.542 --> 07:42.580
- Was beginning to think it was never gonna happen.
- Man! That's tasty!

07:42.671 --> 07:44.583
That's 100% pinot noir.
Single vineyard.

07:44.673 --> 07:46.539
They don't even
make it anymore.

07:46.675 --> 07:48.541
- Pinot noir?
- Mm-hmm.

07:48.635 --> 07:50.547
- Then how come it's white?
- Oh, Jesus.

07:50.637 --> 07:52.503
Don't ask questions like that
up in wine country.

07:52.639 --> 07:55.928
- They'll think you're some kind of dumbshit.
- Just tell me.

07:56.017 --> 07:58.930
Color in red wines
comes from the skins.

07:59.020 --> 08:01.854
This juice, on the other hand,
is free run,

08:01.940 --> 08:04.933
so that there's no skin contact
during fermentation...

08:06.444 --> 08:08.902
<i>Did you read the latest draft,
by the way?</i>

08:09.030 --> 08:10.942
<i>- Oh, yeah. Yeah.
- And?</i>

08:11.032 --> 08:12.944
It's great.

08:13.034 --> 08:15.947
I mean, there are so many improvements.
It's much tighter.

08:16.037 --> 08:18.324
Just seems... I don't know,
more congealed or something.

08:18.415 --> 08:22.910
Mm-hmm. What about the new ending?
Did you like that?

08:23.003 --> 08:27.543
Oh, yeah. New ending vastly superior
to the old ending.

08:27.632 --> 08:29.544
There is no new ending.

08:29.634 --> 08:32.592
Page 750 on
is exactly the same.

08:34.972 --> 08:37.181
Well, maybe
it just seemed new...

08:37.267 --> 08:39.884
because everything leading up to it
was so different?

08:39.977 --> 08:41.970
Yeah!
That must be it!

08:45.775 --> 08:47.641
Whoa.
Why are we getting off?

08:47.777 --> 08:50.645
- Uh, I just wanna make one quick stop.
- For what?

08:50.780 --> 08:53.693
- I just thought we could say a quick hello to my mother.
- Your mother?

08:53.783 --> 08:55.649
<i>Look, it's her birthday
tomorrow. Okay?</i>

08:55.785 --> 08:58.994
<i>- And I don't feel right driving by and not stopping in.
- Okay.</i>

08:59.122 --> 09:01.990
<i>- It'll take a second. She's right off the freeway.
- Okay!</i>

09:02.083 --> 09:04.996
<i>I didn't know it was her birthday.
How old is she gonna be?</i>

09:05.086 --> 09:08.079
<i>Oh, 70-something.</i>

09:13.845 --> 09:17.179
Oh. Here, hold these
for just a second.

09:32.989 --> 09:34.981
Thank you.

09:46.002 --> 09:47.868
