not to come to the wedding,

45:06.495 --> 45:12.082
so just in case you were dreading some sort
of, you know, run-in or something like that,

45:12.168 --> 45:14.080
well, you worry no more,

45:14.170 --> 45:16.082
because I'm not
gonna be there.

45:16.172 --> 45:19.711
It's my little wedding gift
to you and what's-his-name.

45:19.800 --> 45:22.133
What is his name?

45:23.346 --> 45:25.258
<i>Ken.</i>

45:25.348 --> 45:27.260
Ken! Right.

45:27.350 --> 45:29.262
Ken.

45:29.352 --> 45:31.264
I'm gonna
hang up now, Miles.

45:31.354 --> 45:34.722
No... You know, it's just...
I-I-I heard about this...

45:34.815 --> 45:37.478
for the first time, uh, today.

45:37.568 --> 45:39.480
Uh, your getting remarried,
that is.

45:39.570 --> 45:43.985
And, uh, I was
kind of taken aback.

45:44.075 --> 45:47.159
Just... Hard to believe.

45:49.747 --> 45:53.206
I guess I thought maybe
there was still a chance...

45:53.292 --> 45:55.204
for us
somewhere down the road.

45:55.294 --> 45:57.661
And I just, uh...

45:57.797 --> 45:59.709
- Miles.
- Huh?

45:59.799 --> 46:02.712
Maybe it is better if you don't come
to the wedding.

46:05.471 --> 46:08.384
All righty, Vicki.
Whatever you say.

46:08.474 --> 46:10.466
You're the boss.

46:20.820 --> 46:23.278
Huh?
I don't know.

46:23.364 --> 46:26.152
Welcome back.

46:26.242 --> 46:28.154
Take it easy.

46:30.329 --> 46:32.992
- Are you okay, Miles?
- Yes. I'm fine.

46:33.082 --> 46:35.074
Thank you.

46:38.671 --> 46:40.958
- Excuse us, gentlemen.
- Excuse us.

46:41.048 --> 46:42.914
<i>Sure.</i>

46:43.050 --> 46:45.417
- Mmm.
- All right.

46:45.511 --> 46:47.878
Yeah.
Don't take too long.

46:48.014 --> 46:51.428
- All right.
- Okay. Bye, girls.

46:51.517 --> 46:54.055
What the fuck?
What is up with you?

46:54.186 --> 46:56.052
- You remember our little talk outside?
- Yeah...

46:56.188 --> 46:59.226
- Get your shit together, Miles.
- I'm fine. I'm fine.

46:59.317 --> 47:00.933
Where were you?

47:01.027 --> 47:03.064
Bathroom.

47:04.155 --> 47:06.067
Did you drink and dial?

47:06.157 --> 47:07.773
Hmm?

47:07.908 --> 47:10.241
- No.
- Why do you always have to do this?

47:10.328 --> 47:12.695
Victoria is gone.
Gone.

47:12.788 --> 47:15.201
Poof! In the wind.

47:15.291 --> 47:18.409
I mean, you are blowing a great
opportunity here with Maya.

47:18.502 --> 47:20.414
Maya... Fuckin' Maya...
She's great!

47:20.504 --> 47:23.417
She's cool, she's funny,
she knows wine.

47:23.507 --> 47:25.840
What is this morose,
come-down bullshit?

47:25.926 --> 47:28.339
These girls
wanna party with us.

47:28.429 --> 47:30.512
Huh?

47:30.598 --> 47:33.716
And what was that 10-minute lecture on,
what, Vouvrays?

47:33.809 --> 47:36.517
Are you kidding me?
Who gives a fuck?

47:36.604 --> 47:39.938
Let's just say that I'm uncomfortable
with the whole scenario.

47:40.024 --> 47:42.937
Have you forgotten all the bad
times you had with Victoria,

47:43.027 --> 47:45.565
how small
she could make you feel?

47:45.654 --> 47:48.567
Isn't that why you had the affair
with Brenda in the first place?

47:48.657 --> 47:50.569
Shut up. Shut your face.
Shut up.

47:50.659 --> 47:52.776
Have you even noticed
how Maya's looking at you?

47:52.870 --> 47:55.783
Now, come on, man.
You've got her on the hook.

47:55.873 --> 47:58.206
Reel her in.
Let's ratchet this up a notch.

47:58.292 --> 48:02.036
Here.
Drink some <i>agua fria.</i>

48:04.090 --> 48:06.582
Hey!

48:06.717 --> 48:08.629
- Hey!
- Mmm.

48:08.719 --> 48:13.214
Ah. Well, so, uh,
shall we get some dessert?

48:13.307 --> 48:17.221
Uh, well, we were thinking, um, uh,
why don't we go back to my place?

48:17.311 --> 48:20.054
I've got wine, some insane cheeses,
music, whatever.

48:20.147 --> 48:22.059
Yeah!

48:24.151 --> 48:27.485
Waiter!

48:41.585 --> 48:43.497
Come here.

48:43.587 --> 48:45.453
Uh-huh.

48:45.589 --> 48:47.831
- One for you, three for me.
- Mmm.

48:49.051 --> 48:50.963
You sure
you wanna do this?

48:57.560 --> 48:59.472
- We're here!
<i>- Hey!</i>

48:59.562 --> 49:01.929
- Hey!
- Where were you guys?

49:02.022 --> 49:06.266
Oh, we took a couple of wrong turns,
thanks to Magellan here.

49:06.360 --> 49:08.352
- Hi.
- Hi.

49:08.487 --> 49:10.353
- Oh, Miles.
- Yeah?

49:10.489 --> 49:13.357
- Maya's in the back, just past the kitchen.
- Okay.

49:13.492 --> 49:15.404
Thanks.

49:24.420 --> 49:26.332
Hi.

49:26.422 --> 49:28.414
Hey.

49:28.549 --> 49:31.337
- Oh, has she got anything good? <i>
- Oh, yeah.</i>

49:31.427 --> 49:34.295
<i>Steph's way into
pinots and Syrahs.</i>

49:34.388 --> 49:36.300
- Hey, Steph!
<i>- Yeah?</i>

49:36.390 --> 49:40.225
- Can we really open anything we want? <i>
- Yeah, yeah. Anything.</i>

49:40.311 --> 49:42.644
<i>Uh, except
the Richebourg.</i>

49:42.730 --> 49:46.189
Richebourg? She has a Richebourg?
Holy mackerel.

49:46.275 --> 49:48.187
<i>I've completely
underestimated Stephanie.</i>

49:48.277 --> 49:51.566
<i>Oh, good Lord.
Um, look at that.</i>

49:53.657 --> 49:57.822
<i>I think...
this guy's more our speed.</i>

49:57.912 --> 49:59.824
Andrew Murray.

49:59.914 --> 50:02.372
Well, okay.
All right.

50:04.960 --> 50:07.873
So, what gems do you have
in your collection?

50:07.963 --> 50:11.127
Oh, it's really not much
of a collection, you know.

50:11.217 --> 50:14.085
I mean, more like a small gathering
in a cabinet.

50:14.220 --> 50:17.133
No,
I've never really had the wallet for that.

50:17.223 --> 50:19.636
I just have to live
bottle to bottle.

50:19.725 --> 50:22.138
I've got things
I'm saving, definitely.

50:22.228 --> 50:26.643
I guess the star would be
a 1961 Cheval Blanc.

50:26.732 --> 50:29.600
You've got a '61 Cheval Blanc,
and it's just sitting there?

50:29.735 --> 50:31.601
- Yes, I do.
- Go get it.

50:31.737 --> 50:33.649
- Okay.
- I'm serious! Hurry!

50:33.739 --> 50:35.651
All right.
I would, I would.

50:35.741 --> 50:38.734
